{
  "framework": "pcc",
  "research_question": "What is the methodological rigour of systematic reviews evaluating health outcomes associated with environmental exposures, as assessed by adherence to established systematic review guidelines and risk of bias evaluation frameworks? [META-SR NOTE: This is a review-of-reviews. The TARGET POPULATION for inclusion is SYSTEMATIC REVIEWS themselves (not primary studies). An eligible article MUST be a systematic review, meta-analysis, or umbrella review OF environmental-health studies. Treat the phrases 'systematic review', 'meta-analysis', 'scoping review', 'umbrella review' appearing in the title/abstract as POSITIVE inclusion signals indicating the article IS a review — not as method statements about how the authors conducted their own work. Primary empirical studies (cohort, case-control, RCT, lab experiments on environmental exposures themselves) should be EXCLUDED because they are not reviews.]",
